SIMPLE: chromite
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chromite
<hw>Chro"mite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A black submetallic mineral consisting of oxide
of chromium and iron; -- called also <altname>chromic
iron</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound or salt of chromous
hydroxide regarded as an acid.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chromium</ent>⟦br⟧
